Now I have a complete picture of the codebase. Let me design the implementation plan.

---

## Lexical Editor Upgrade — Implementation Plan

### Answers to your questions before the plan

**Tier scope:** Implement Tier 1 fully and Tier 2 items 6, 7, 8, 9, 10. Skip Tier 3 (slash commands and collapsible sections add complexity that exceeds their value for a first pass; justify alignment is a one-liner you can do anytime).

**Mobile toolbar:** Horizontal scroll + floating selection toolbar. This is the right call. The current `flex-wrap: wrap` approach breaks badly once you add 8 more buttons.

**Slash commands:** Skip for now. They require a custom plugin with significant complexity. The floating toolbar on selection already solves the mobile discoverability problem.

**Floating link editor:** Inline popup (not a modal). It should appear anchored below the selected text or the link node, with URL input + confirm + remove actions. A modal interrupts flow and is wrong for a writing tool.

---

### Architecture decisions before writing a line of code

**The `ToolbarForEdit.jsx` problem:** This file is a stripped-down, lower-quality duplicate of `Toolbar.jsx`. It is used in `EditJournal`, but after this upgrade you should consolidate — make `Toolbar.jsx` accept an optional `addUploadedImagePath` prop (already has it) and retire `ToolbarForEdit.jsx`. The edit journal flow should just use the main `Toolbar`.

**Shared node list:** The biggest change across the codebase is that every `LexicalComposer` config (App.jsx, ContentView.jsx x2, ChapterEditor.jsx, ChapterReader.jsx, editJournal.jsx) needs the same expanded node list. Rather than scatter this and create drift again, you should extract a shared constants file.

**New file: `client/src/components/HomePage/Editor/editorConfig.js`**

This file exports:
- `EDITOR_NODES` — the canonical node array for write mode
- `VIEWER_NODES` — same set but for read-only instances (can be identical)
- `EDITOR_THEME` — the single source of truth for theme CSS class mapping

Every composer in the app imports from this file. When you add a new node type in the future, you change one file.

**Image paste/drop plugin:** Rather than a new ImagePlugin, add paste and drop handling directly inside the existing `ImagePlugin.jsx` or create a sibling `PasteImagePlugin.jsx`.

---

### Phase 1 — Package installation + shared config foundation

**Goal:** Install new packages and create the shared config module. No visible change to users yet. All tests should still pass.

**Step 1.1 — Install new Lexical packages**

Run in `client/`:
```
npm install @lexical/list @lexical/link @lexical/markdown @lexical/code @lexical/html
```

Keep versions pinned to `^0.17.0` to match existing packages. `@lexical/html` is optional but useful for future clipboard operations.

**Step 1.2 — Create `editorConfig.js`**

New file: `client/src/components/HomePage/Editor/editorConfig.js`

```js
import { HeadingNode, QuoteNode } from '@lexical/rich-text';
import { ListNode, ListItemNode } from '@lexical/list';
import { LinkNode, AutoLinkNode } from '@lexical/link';
import { HorizontalRuleNode } from '@lexical/react/LexicalHorizontalRulePlugin';
import { CodeNode, CodeHighlightNode } from '@lexical/code';
import ImageNode from './nodes/ImageNode';
import MentionNode from './nodes/MentionNode';

export const EDITOR_NODES = [
  ImageNode,
  MentionNode,
  HeadingNode,
  QuoteNode,
  ListNode,
  ListItemNode,
  LinkNode,
  AutoLinkNode,
  HorizontalRuleNode,
  CodeNode,
  CodeHighlightNode,
];

// Read-only instances need the same nodes to deserialize stored content correctly
export const VIEWER_NODES = EDITOR_NODES;

export const EDITOR_THEME = {
  paragraph: 'editor-paragraph',
  heading: {
    h1: 'editor-heading-h1',
    h2: 'editor-heading-h2',
    h3: 'editor-heading-h3',
  },
  quote: 'editor-quote',
  text: {
    bold: 'editor-text-bold',
    italic: 'editor-text-italic',
    underline: 'editor-text-underline',
    strikethrough: 'editor-text-strikethrough',
    code: 'editor-text-code',
  },
  list: {
    nested: {
      listitem: 'editor-nested-listitem',
    },
    ol: 'editor-list-ol',
    ul: 'editor-list-ul',
    listitem: 'editor-listitem',
    listitemChecked: 'editor-listitem-checked',
    listitemUnchecked: 'editor-listitem-unchecked',
  },
  link: 'editor-link',
  code: 'editor-code',
  codeHighlight: {
    atrule: 'editor-tokenize-atrule',
    attr: 'editor-tokenize-attr',
    boolean: 'editor-tokenize-boolean',
    builtin: 'editor-tokenize-builtin',
    cdata: 'editor-tokenize-cdata',
    char: 'editor-tokenize-char',
    class: 'editor-tokenize-class',
    'class-name': 'editor-tokenize-class-name',
    comment: 'editor-tokenize-comment',
    constant: 'editor-tokenize-constant',
    deleted: 'editor-tokenize-deleted',
    doctype: 'editor-tokenize-doctype',
    entity: 'editor-tokenize-entity',
    function: 'editor-tokenize-function',
    important: 'editor-tokenize-important',
    inserted: 'editor-tokenize-inserted',
    keyword: 'editor-tokenize-keyword',
    namespace: 'editor-tokenize-namespace',
    number: 'editor-tokenize-number',
    operator: 'editor-tokenize-operator',
    prolog: 'editor-tokenize-prolog',
    property: 'editor-tokenize-property',
    punctuation: 'editor-tokenize-punctuation',
    regex: 'editor-tokenize-regex',
    selector: 'editor-tokenize-selector',
    string: 'editor-tokenize-string',
    symbol: 'editor-tokenize-symbol',
    tag: 'editor-tokenize-tag',
    url: 'editor-tokenize-url',
    variable: 'editor-tokenize-variable',
  },
};
```

**Step 1.3 — Update `App.jsx`**

Replace the inline `editorTheme` object and the `editorConfig` with imports from the new file:

```js
// Remove the inline editorTheme and editorConfig objects
import { EDITOR_NODES, EDITOR_THEME } from './components/HomePage/Editor/editorConfig';

const editorConfig = {
  namespace: "MyLexicalEditor",
  theme: EDITOR_THEME,
  nodes: EDITOR_NODES,
  onError(error) { throw error; },
};
```

**Step 1.4 — Update all other LexicalComposer instances**

There are 5 other places with inline node arrays. All need to import from `editorConfig.js`:

- `ContentView.jsx` — `RepostSourceViewer` instance (line ~413) and `ContentViewer` instance (line ~588): replace inline `nodes:` with `VIEWER_NODES`, replace inline `theme:` with `EDITOR_THEME`
- `ChapterReader.jsx` — `editorConfig` object (line ~159)
- `ChapterEditor.jsx` — `editorTheme` and node list at the top
- `editJournal.jsx` — `theme` object and node list

This phase has zero UI changes but establishes correctness. Any content saved with new node types in the future will render properly in read-only views.

---

### Phase 2 — Tier 1 features: Lists, Strikethrough, Horizontal Rule, Undo/Redo buttons

**Goal:** The four quick wins that writers need most. All are self-contained and testable independently.

**Step 2.1 — Register new plugins in `RichTextEditor.jsx`**

Add these plugin imports and JSX inside the `editor-shell` div, alongside `ImagePlugin` and `MentionPlugin`:

```jsx
import { ListPlugin } from '@lexical/react/LexicalListPlugin';
import { CheckListPlugin } from '@lexical/react/LexicalCheckListPlugin';
import { HorizontalRulePlugin } from '@lexical/react/LexicalHorizontalRulePlugin';

// Inside editor-shell:
<ListPlugin />
<CheckListPlugin />
<HorizontalRulePlugin />
